methods.name: RSADecryptPrivateCRT(Byte[] Data)
methods.summary: Low level RSA Decryption function for use with private key. Uses CRT and is Much faster. Should never be used; Because without padding RSA is vulnerable to attacks. Use with caution.

params.value: Data to encrypt. Length must be less than Modulus size in octets.

methods.name: RSAProcess(Byte[] PlainText, bool usePrivate)
methods.summary: Low level RSA Process function for use with private key. Should never be used; Because without padding RSA is vulnerable to attacks. Use with caution.

params.value: Data to encrypt. Length must be less than Modulus size in octets.
True to use Private key, else Public.
